  • 2024 PCMag Editor's Choice - Praised for its outstanding value, delivering sharp 2K resolution and a comprehensive feature set.
  • Compact, Versatile, Weatherproof - The Tapo C120 is a compact camera suitable for indoor and outdoor use, featuring an IP66 rating for withstanding rain, dust, and rugged conditions.
  • Magnetic Base for Flexible Mounting - Easily attach the C120 camera to any metal surface with its magnetic base. Versatile mounting on railings, frames, or even the refrigerator.
  • 2K QHD 4MP Resolution - Crystal-clear detail in every shot. Capture every moment with stunning 2K quality that ensures even the finest details are never missed.
  • Starlight Color Night Vision - The built-in Starlight sensor delivers bright, colorful video at night, with two spotlights for extra illumination in darker conditions.
  • Invisible IR Mode - Get night vision up to 30ft with IR light. If the red light is distracting, switch to invisible mode for discreet monitoring.
  • No-Cost Person/Pet/Vehicle Detection - The Tapo C120 uses AI to detect people, pets, or vehicles for free. Customize alerts to focus on specific objects and reduce notifications.
  • Full Duplex 2-Way Audio - Talk in real time, just like a phone call, for smooth communication with delivery personnel, kids, pets, and more.
  • Local or Cloud Storage - Store recordings on a MicroSD card up to 512GB (not included) or via the Tapo Care Cloud subscription. [Check TP-Link FAQ for MicroSD compatibility before purchase.]

Customer ratings by feature

Additional details

If you are looking for a compact, feature packed, versatile camera solution, the Tapo C120 is the ideal camera for you. The camera includes premium features at no additional cost, such as its free person/pet/vehicle detection, powered by AI processing as well as a suite of other features including full duplex two-way audio, Alexa and Google compatibility and light and sound alarms. Monitor where you want with custom monitoring zones and add additional privacy with privacy zones. The camera image sensor is 1/29.'' progressive scan CMOS starlight sensor. The camera lens focal length is 3.17 mm and has a 1.65 aperture. The camera field of view is 120° diagonal, 103° horizontal, and 55° vertical. The night vision is 850 nm IR LED (30 ft / 9 m), 940 nm IR LED (30 ft / 9 m). The camera has full color night vision. The camera frame rate is 20 fps (self-adaptive according to brightness). The camera's digital zoom is 12x. The camera's video compression is H.264. The camera has a live view. The image enhancement features 3K DNR and WDR. This camera has two-way audio with noise cancellation. The siren level is 96dB (level measured at 4-inch/10-cm distance). This camera's AI detections include motion detection, person detection, line-crossing detection, baby cry detection, vehicle detection, pet detection, meow detection, bark detection, and glass-breaking detection. This camera supports the 802.11b/g/n protocol. The wireless rates are as follows: 11 Mbps (802.11 b), 54 Mbps (802.11 g), 72.2 Mbps (802.11n). Wireless security includes WPA, WPA2-PSK. The security features include 128-bit AES encryption with SSL/TLS and on-device machine learning. The packaging contents include 1 Tapo C120 Camera, 1 5.0 V, 1.0 A power adapter, 3m (9.84ft) Type-C wire, 4 mounting anchors, 4 mounting screws, 2 cable organizers, 1 mounting template, 1 iron camera base, 3M adhesive, detaching pin, 1 quick start guide.

      • DeeJay
        4.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
        Good cameras, especially for the price point.
        Reviewed in the United States on March 2, 2025
        Style: White
        These maintain a solid WiFi connection with decent, though not fantastic, image quality. They are also compatible with 3rd party NAS devices by IP, which is a definite plus. The addition of LED lights (which can be either manually or automatically triggered) enhances the... See more
        These maintain a solid WiFi connection with decent, though not fantastic, image quality. They are also compatible with 3rd party NAS devices by IP, which is a definite plus. The addition of LED lights (which can be either manually or automatically triggered) enhances the image at night, but it's still really meant for close-in use. Outside of 20-30 feet, the image is generally too blurry to be of any real use. During the day, that probably extends to around 45 feet.

        Although I use these with a Synology NAS (Surveillance Station), the Tapo app is not bad. It allows connecting to the cameras free of charge, including remotely, and configuring the various settings. Enabling cloud recording requires a subscription which is based on how many cameras you have. Compared to other cloud-based security subscriptions, it is reasonably priced.

        While construction overall seems sturdy, my only real complaints are that the adjustment screws cannot be tightened. This means the cameras are subject to moving around if the wind hits them when mounted outdoors. I also dislike that the mount has only one screw hole instead of two. The manufacturer pushes the magnetic mounting base, but that's not always the best solution (particularly outdoors), so having 2 pre-drilled screw holes on the base, instead of just one, would be nice.

      • T. Tozawa
        5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
        RTSP Support and excellent night quality
        Reviewed in the United States on December 19, 2024
        Style: White
        EDIT: Some extra opinions now that I’ve been using this for a longer period of time. In short, it’s been working awesome. I have it continuously recording and when at home I sometimes stream it for a few hours to check the outside of my home and everything works as it... See more
        EDIT: Some extra opinions now that I’ve been using this for a longer period of time. In short, it’s been working awesome. I have it continuously recording and when at home I sometimes stream it for a few hours to check the outside of my home and everything works as it should. The video lag when I’m streaming is as low as 1-2 seconds and if you’re running a stream for a long time, it can go up to around 5 seconds lag. But re-starting the stream fixes it and the lag is honestly not bad.

        Video quality is great in the day and at night it’s surprisingly excellent. You can see a lot of detail with just a few street lights outside. And indoors, even in a completely pitch black room, you can clearly see everything.

        I ended up buying another camera since it’s been working so well. Using the app, it’s easy to set up recording times and other settings such as detection methods like general motion or when a person enters the frame. The one feature I really love is that you can set the zones for detection. Like if your video frame has a lot of movement on the top that you want to ignore, but the bottom of the frame has a walkway to your property, you can frame out what area you want the detection. It works great. Notifications are quick and accurate and the overall app UI is simple and easy to use.

        A note about the memory card. If you’re going to be using it to record continuously, and even if you’re not, get an endurance microSD which are made for the constant rewrites. I got a 256gb Samsung one and recording at 2K quality, it was around 18-19gb for one day. Usable memory is about 220gb so you can get roughly 12 days of footage you can always look back on.

        ORIGINAL REVIEW:
        I wanted a security camera with RTSP support and can confirm this works. I tested it out with VLC Player and it worked great. Minimal lag and picture quality is great, especially at night. I tried in a room with only light from a monitor and you could clearly see. App and options seems solid. I did have initial problems connecting to Wi-Fi and had to try two times but once it connected I had no issues. The camera itself is very light and the magnetic base works well. Solid and easy angle adjustments. The price is so cheap for the quality you get.

        Camera is fantastic. Great features. You can separately set zones for motion, people, pets, and vehicles. You can also set a privacy zone -an area that the camera will not record. I bought a Sandisk High Endurance 128GB for around $15. The camera will loop and overwrite the micro sd card once its full. Even without a subscription you can get a live view on your phone from anywhere and the recordings are local to your SD card. If you need to download a video, your phone just needs to be connected to the same wifi network the camera is connected to. The downloaded video will appear in your phone's camera gallery. I highly recommend this camera. For the price, you can't go wrong. I bought a couple of Ring cameras, set them up, played with the app a little bit. Honestly, I prefer the Tapo cameras. I returned the Ring cameras I bought. By the way, the video and snapshots that you can record are fantastic. Very clear and easy to see details including the night vision videos.
